ors","slug":"general-motors","url":"http:\/\/fortune.com\/tag\/general-motors\/"},"paid":false,"paid_excerpt":"Is the automaker undervalued?","seo":{"seo_title":"Why Buffett and Soros are buying into GM now","seo_description":"Is the automaker undervalued?","seo_keywords":"","seo_news_keywords":"","seo_additional_meta":""},"social":{"encoded_url":"http%3A%2F%2Ffortune.com%2F2015%2F02%2F19%2Fgm-buffett-soros%2F","encoded_shortlink":"http%3A%2F%2Ffor.tn%2F1AKTF0u","encoded_title":"Why+Buffett+and+Soros+are+buying+into+GM%C2%A0now","twitter_text":"Why Buffett and Soros are buying into GM\u00a0now","twitter_via":"FORTUNE","facebook_desc":"Is the automaker undervalued?","facebook_title":"Why Buffett and Soros are buying into GM now"},"format":{"term_id":2710,"name":"Article","slug":"fortune-post-format-article","term_group":0,"term_taxonomy_id":3,"taxonomy":"fortune_post_format","description":"","parent":0,"count":11113,"filter":"raw"},"related_posts":[],"in_article_ad_id":["in-article-ad-997540-0","in-article-ad-997540-1","in-article-ad-997540-2"]}],"latest_news":[{"id":997949,"content_type":"free full","is_magazine_content":"non-magazine","url":"\/2015\/02\/19\/wal-mart-wage-hike-2-million-hours\/","title":"A Wal-Mart worker making $9 an hour would have to work 2.8 million hours to match the CEO\u2019s pay","content":"<p>The world&#8217;s largest retailer <a href=\"http:\/\/fortune.com\/2015\/02\/19\/wal-mart-pay-increase\/\">announced wage hikes<\/a> for its U.S. employees Thursday, raising its minimum hourly wage to at least $9.<\/p>\n<p>Wal-Mart <span class=\"tickershortcode quotecard_hook unprocessed neutral\" data-symbol=\"WMT\">\n\t\t\t\t<span class=\"wrapper trend-wrapper\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<a class=\"exit_trigger_set\" href=\"\/company\/wmt\/\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"ticker\">WMT<\/span>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"change percent\"><\/span>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/a>\n\t\t\t\t<\/span>\n\t\t\t<\/span> made the announcement as part of its latest quarterly earnings report and said the increase will cost the largest private employer in the country about $1 billion.<\/p>\n<p>Just for fun, <em>Fortune<\/em> wondered how many hours it would take a Wal-Mart employee earning the increased minimum salary to earn the same amount of compensation as CEO Doug McMillon. The answer? It would take more than 2.8 million hours of earning $9 per hour to reach the roughly $25.6 million in compensation McMillon earned in 2014, his first year on the job. (That number would come down to roughly 2.6 million hours with next year&#8217;s additional hourly increase.)<\/p>\n<p>For those wondering, there are only 8,760 hours in a calendar year and the U.S. Office of Personnel Management estimates the average number of actual work hours in a year to be 2,087. Using the latter figure, a Wal-Mart employee earning the new minimum hourly wage of $9 per hour would have to work more than 1,360 years in order to equal McMillon&#8217;s 2014 compensation.<br \/>\n<div class=\"video-wrapper\"  data-ratio=\"0.56363636363636\" data-pos=\"12\">\n\t\t\t\t<object id=\"bc-video-4003013008001-12\" class=\"BrightcoveExperience\"><param name=\"bgcolor\" value=\"#FFFFFF\"\/><param name=\"width\" value=\"550\"\/><param name=\"height\" value=\"310\"\/><param name=\"playerID\" value=\"3160175193001\"\/><param name=\"playerKey\" value=\"AQ~~,AAAB668kGak~,LMlvL4u4ShOTHD9z00VquajMOcH97tcW\"\/><param name=\"isVid\" value=\"true\"\/><param name=\"isUI\" value=\"true\"\/><param name=\"videoSmoothing\" value=\"true\"\/><param name=\"seamlessTabbing\" value=\"false\"\/><param name=\"swliveconnect\" value=\"true\"\/><param name=\"dynamicStreaming\" value=\"true\"\/><param name=\"autoStart\" value=\"false\"\/><param name=\"@videoPlayer\" value=\"4003013008001\"\/><param name=\"linkBaseURL\" value=\"http:\/\/for.tn\/1BqBooQ\"\/><param name=\"includeAPI\" value=\"true\"\/><param name=\"templateLoadHandler\" value=\"Fortune_onTemplateLoad\"\/><param name=\"templateReadyHandler\" value=\"Fortune_onTemplateReady\"\/><param name=\"wmode\" value=\"opaque\"\/><param name=\"adServerURL\" value=\"http:\/\/pubads.g.doubleclick.net\/gampad\/ads?env=vp&amp;gdfp_req=1&amp;impl=s&amp;output=xml_vast2&amp;iu=\/8484\/fort\/video_bc\/retail_bc&amp;sz=1000x1&amp;cust_params=tags%3Dbusinessnews%2Cdirect2cashprogram%2Cretailnews%2Cwalmartcheckingaccount%2Cwalmartdirect2cash%2Cwalmartgobank%2Cwalmartincometax%2Cwalmarttaxpreparers%2Cwalmarttaxrefundprogram%2Cwalmarttaxseason%26ch%3Dretail%26topic%3Dwalmartdirect2cash&amp;unviewed_position_start=1&amp;correlator=timestamp\"\/><\/object>\n\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t<script type=\"text\/javascript\">\n\t\t\t\tbrightcove.createExperiences();\n\t\t\t<\/script><\/p>\n<p>The <a href=\"http:\/\/services.corporate-ir.net\/SEC.Enhanced\/SecCapsule.aspx?c=112761&amp;fid=9407967\">total compensation<\/a> for Wal-Mart&#8217;s CEO last year included a base salary of about $950,000, plus more than $23 million in stock awards, along with additional incentives.<\/p>\n<p>McMillon took over for former Wal-Mart CEO Mike Duke a year ago amid a string of <a href=\"http:\/\/fortune.com\/2014\/07\/25\/can-a-new-ceo-rescue-walmarts-u-s-sales\/\">disappointing quarterly U.S. sales numbers<\/a> for the retail giant. McMillon&#8217;s promotion earned him a hefty raise last year after he took home around $10 million a year earlier as head of the company&#8217;s international business. In the most recent quarter, Wal-Mart reported a better-than-expected U.S. sales bump as well as a 1.4% increase in total revenue.<\/p>\n<p>The news comes at a time of intense debate over what constitutes fair pay for low-wage workers and it follows <a href=\"http:\/\/www.nytimes.com\/2014\/10\/17\/business\/walmart-workers-seek-wage-bump.html\">protests last fall<\/a> by Wal-Mart employees seeking a base pay of $15 per hour for all company employees. The company&#8217;s planned wage hike, which will go into effect in April, doesn&#8217;t go quite that far, but it does outpace the federally mandated minimum wage by $1.75 per hour. Wal-Mart also said its minimum wage will go up again next year, to $10\/hour.<\/p>\n<p>Labor groups have long argued that Wal-Mart should pay its low-wage employees more and <em>Fortune&#8217;s<\/em> <a href=\"http:\/\/fortune.com\/2013\/11\/12\/why-wal-mart-can-afford-to-give-its-workers-a-50-raise\/\">Stephen Gandel wrote<\/a> two years ago that the retail giant could even afford to increase its workers&#8217; pay by 50% without disappointing its shareholders and bondholders.<\/p>\n","time":{"pretty":"February 19, 2015","published":"2015-02-19 04:08:27","updated":"2015-02-19 04:08:27","minute":"4:08 PM EST","is_same_day":true,"is_home_pop":true},"comment_url":"http:\/\/fortune.com\/2015\/02\/19\/wal-mart-wage-hike-2-million-hours\/","absolute_url":"http:\/\/fortune.com\/2015\/02\/19\/wal-mart-wage-hike-2-million-hours\/","redirect_url":"","partner":"","outbrain_url":"http:\/\/fortune.com\/2015\/02\/19\/wal-mart-wage-hike-2-million-hours\/","outbrain_footer":true,"outbrain_right_rail":true,"short_title":"Here\u2019s how long it would take a Wal-Mart worker to earn the CEO\u2019s pay","post_type":"post","featured_type":"video","featured_video":{"html":"<div class=\"video-wrapper\"  data-ratio=\"1\" data-pos=\"13\">\n\t\t\t\t<object id=\"bc-video-4069675262001-13\" class=\"BrightcoveExperience\"><param name=\"bgcolor\" value=\"#FFFFFF\"\/><param name=\"width\" value=\"100%\"\/><param name=\"height\" value=\"100%\"\/><param name=\"playerID\" value=\"3160175193001\"\/><param name=\"playerKey\" value=\"AQ~~,AAAB668kGak~,LMlvL4u4ShOTHD9z00VquajMOcH97tcW\"\/><param name=\"isVid\" value=\"true\"\/><param name=\"isUI\" value=\"true\"\/><param name=\"videoSmoothing\" value=\"true\"\/><param name=\"seamlessTabbing\" value=\"false\"\/><param name=\"swliveconnect\" value=\"true\"\/><param name=\"dynamicStreaming\" value=\"true\"\/><param name=\"autoStart\" value=\"false\"\/><param name=\"@videoPlayer\" value=\"4069675262001\"\/>