way.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>But the networks are trying to offset shrinking ad revenue. \u201cIt is a way to keep the revenue from going down as much as the ratings,\u201d one top executive at a major cable programmer told the <em>WSJ<\/em>. \u201cThe only way we can do it is to double down and stretch the unit load a little more.\u201d<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"http:\/\/www.wsj.com\/articles\/cable-tv-shows-are-sped-up-to-squeeze-in-more-ads-1424301320\" target=\"_blank\">According to Nielsen<\/a>, the average commercial time on cable TV per hour has increased to 15.8 minutes in 2014 from 14.5 minutes five years ago, with networks such as MTV, TV Land and Spike now containing over 20 minutes of non-programming content an hour.<\/p>\n","time":{"pretty":"February 19, 2015","published":"2015-02-19 04:07:11","updated":"2015-02-19 04:07:11","minute":"4:07 PM EST","is_same_day":true,"is_home_pop":true},"comment_url":"http:\/\/fortune.com\/2015\/02\/19\/how-cable-networks-are-cramming-more-ads-in-your-favorite-shows\/","absolute_url":"http:\/\/fortune.com\/2015\/02\/19\/how-cable-networks-are-cramming-more-ads-in-your-favorite-shows\/","redirect_url":"","partner":"","outbrain_url":"http:\/\/fortune.com\/2015\/02\/19\/how-cable-networks-are-cramming-more-ads-in-your-favorite-shows\/","outbrain_footer":true,"outbrain_right_rail":false,"short_title":"How cable networks are cramming more ads in your favorite shows","post_type":"post","featured_type":"image","featured_image":{"src":"https:\/\/fortunedotcom.files.wordpress.com\/2015\/02\/87301848.jpg?quality=80&w=840&h=485&crop=1","class":"featured-img-article_full","credit":"Photograph by Getty Images\/Image Source","caption":"","attach_id":"998542"},"excerpt":"<p>Here&#8217;s why Kramer, Jerry and George might sound as if they&#8217;ve been inhaling helium.<\/p>\n","authors":[{"id":"998518","url":"http:\/\/fortune.com\/author\/tessa-berensontime\/","name":"Tessa Berenson\/TIME","twitter":"","gplus":"","email":"","thumbnail":"<img alt='' src